<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC) No 1658/82 of 10 June 1982 supplementing by provisions on combined transport Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 on the granting of aids for transport by rail, road and inland waterway </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1658/82, millega lisatakse m&auml;&auml;rusele (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 toetuste andmise kohta raudtee-, maantee- ja siseveetranspordile kombineeritud transporti k&auml;sitlevad s&auml;tted 10. juuni 1982 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 of 4 June 1970 on the granting of aids for transport by rail, road and inland waterway (1), and in particular Article 3 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 4. juuni 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 toetuste andmise kohta raudtee-, maantee- ja siseveetranspordile, (1) eriti selle artiklit 3, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (4), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (4) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the various systems and technologies for combined transport bring benefits for the Community in general, inter alia by reducing congestion on certain roads, conserving energy and allowing better use to be made of railway capacity; </inglise>
<eesti> kombineeritud transpordi erinevad s&uuml;steemid ja tehnoloogiad toovad kasu tervele &uuml;hendusele, aidates muu hulgas v&auml;hendada teatavatel maanteedel tekkivaid liiklusummikuid ja hoida kokku energiat ning v&otilde;imaldades paremini &auml;ra kasutada raudtee l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imet; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the investment required for the development of combined transport should accordingly be encouraged; whereas it is therefore essential that aid granted by a Member State or through State resources can be made available to the undertakings concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> seet&otilde;ttu tuleks soodustada kombineeritud transpordi arendamiseks vajalikke investeeringuid; seep&auml;rast on oluline, et liikmesriikide poolt v&otilde;i riigi varudest antav toetus oleks asjaomastele ettev&otilde;tjatele k&auml;ttesaadav; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 provides that Member States may grant aid to assist the development of transport systems and technologies that are more economic for the Community but restricts such aid to the experimental phase; whereas, for the development of combined transport, allowance should also be made for an initial operating phase which is sufficiently long to enable such transport to qualify for better conditions in the haulage market; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 n&auml;hakse ette, et liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad anda toetust &uuml;hendusele soodsamate transpordis&uuml;steemide ja -tehnoloogiate arendamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks, kuid s&auml;testatakse, et toetust saab anda ainult katseperioodil; kombineeritud transpordi arendamiseks tuleks ette n&auml;ha ka esialgne kasutusperiood, mis on piisavalt pikk, et k&otilde;nealune transport saaks omandada paremad tingimused veoturgudel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is therefore necessary to adjust the Community provisions relating to aids, </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast on vaja kohandada toetusi k&auml;sitlevaid &uuml;henduse s&auml;tteid, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The following subparagraph is hereby added to Article 3 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 1 lisatakse j&auml;rgmine l&otilde;ik: </eesti>
<inglise> '(e) where the aids are granted as a temporary measure and designed to facilitate the development of combined transport, such aids having to relate to investment in the following fields: </inglise>
<eesti> "(e) juhul, kui toetust antakse ajutiselt ning see on m&otilde;eldud kombineeritud transpordi arendamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks ja on seotud investeeringutega j&auml;rgmistes valdkondades: </eesti>
<inglise> - infrastructure, </inglise>
<eesti> - infrastruktuur, </eesti>
<inglise> - the fixed and moveable facilities necessary for trans-shipment. </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;mberlaadimiseks vajalikud p&uuml;si- v&otilde;i teisaldatavad vahendid. </eesti>
<inglise> Before 31 December 1986 the Commission shall make a progress report to the Council on the application of this provision. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon esitab enne 1986. aasta 31. detsembrit n&otilde;ukogule aruande k&auml;esoleva s&auml;tte kohaldamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> In the light of that report and in view of the temporary nature of the system provided for in this Regulation, the Council shall decide, on a proposal from the Commission, on the system to be applied subsequently and, if necessary, on the procedures to be adopted for terminating that system. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu teeb komisjoni ettepanekul ning k&otilde;nealust aruannet ja k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud s&uuml;steemi ajutist laadi silmas pidades otsuse edaspidi kohaldatava s&uuml;steemi kohta ning vajaduse korral korra kohta, mis v&otilde;etakse vastu selle s&uuml;steemi l&otilde;petamiseks." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from 1 July 1982. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse alates 1. juulist 1982. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 10 June 1982. </inglise>
<eesti> Luxembourg, 10. juuni 1982 </eesti>
